The paper deals with optimization problems on graphs, specifically the MST-interdiction problem and its application to metric TSP interdiction. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories related to graph algorithms and optimization, such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.GT (computational game theory). Additionally, the paper's use of LP-based approximation algorithms and its analysis of approximation ratios suggest that it could also belong to the category of cs.LG (machine learning), which often involves optimization problems and mathematical analysis.
